<h2 id="the-show">The Show</h2>
<p>At the end of the day The Lunicorn threw a memorable night where we all got to meet up and have some fun. The show itself was inspired by classic game shows, spiced up with short, funny video clips where Matt played all the roles. Heck, there even was a house band to make the transitions smooth.</p>

<p>The first half of the show was a head-to-head battle between the startup hubs Epicenter and Startup Campus, where representatives from the two hubs had to answer awkward questions about how well they knew each other, followed by a â€œpitching competitionâ€ where they had to pitch silly startups as if they were the founders. For the second part of the show the founder of Tise and the former CEO of Tidal entered the stage for a â€œcosy couch conversationâ€ about their journeys.</p>

